      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(github-copilot): prefer live model catalog",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- prefer GitHub Copilot's live `/models` catalog rows for visible model metadata\n- keep bounded static Copilot rows as a degraded fallback when live discovery is disabled, unauthenticated, or unavailable\n- merge live + fallback rows by model id with live metadata winning on duplicates, so stale fallback rows cannot mask live context windows/reasoning/input data\n- preserve explicit user config as the operator override path\n- add regression coverage for retained fallback rows, discovery-disabled fallback behavior, and live-first duplicate handling\n\nFixes #88548.\n\n## Tests\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/github-copilot/models.test.ts extensions/github-copilot/index.test.ts extensions/github-copilot/provider-policy-api.test.ts src/commands/models/list.provider-catalog.test.ts src/commands/model-picker.test.ts`\n  - 154 tests passed\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.extensions.json extensions/github-copilot`\n  - 0 warnings, 0 errors\n\nNote: `pnpm exec oxlint ...` attempted to fetch optional platform packages and hit local VM disk pressure (`ERR_PNPM_ENOSPC`, filesystem ~98% full). The local checked-in `node_modules/.bin/oxlint` binary was present and completed successfully.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed:** GitHub Copilot model visibility and metadata now use live `/models` rows first, while retaining bounded static fallback rows only for degraded discovery/offline cases. Duplicate ids keep the live row, preventing stale fallback metadata such as old GPT-5.5 context windows from masking live values.\n- **Real environment tested:** Local OpenClaw source checkout on macOS/Darwin arm64, Node v22.22.2, pnpm v11.2.2, authenticated GitHub CLI token for a real Copilot-enabled account. The live Copilot API base URL resolved to `https://api.enterprise.githubcopilot.com`.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch:**\n\n```bash\nGH_TOKEN=\"$(gh auth token)\" pnpm exec tsx -e '\nimport { resolveCopilotApiToken } from \"./extensions/github-copilot/token.ts\";\nimport { fetchCopilotModelCatalog } from \"./extensions/github-copilot/models.ts\";\nasync function main() {\n  const githubToken = process.env.GH_TOKEN;\n  if (!githubToken) throw new Error(\"missing GH_TOKEN from gh auth\");\n  const token = await resolveCopilotApiToken({ githubToken, env: process.env });\n  const rows = await fetchCopilotModelCatalog({ copilotApiToken: token.token, baseUrl: token.baseUrl });\n  const interesting = rows.filter((row) => [\"gpt-5.5\", \"claude-opus-4.7-1m-internal\", \"gpt-5.4\", \"gpt-5.3-codex\"].includes(row.id));\n  console.log(JSON.stringify({\n    proof: \"patched github-copilot fetchCopilotModelCatalog live /models\",\n    baseUrl: token.baseUrl,\n    modelCount: rows.length,\n    selected: interesting.map((row) => ({\n      id: row.id,\n      name: row.name,\n      api: row.api,\n      reasoning: row.reasoning,\n      contextWindow: row.contextWindow,\n      maxTokens: row.maxTokens,\n      input: row.input,\n      compat: row.compat,\n      thinkingLevelMap: row.thinkingLevelMap,\n    })),\n    firstFiveIds: rows.slice(0, 5).map((row) => row.id),\n  }, null, 2));\n}\nmain().catch((err) => { console.error(err instanceof Error ? err.message : err); process.exit(1); });\n'\n```\n\n- **Evidence after fix:** Copied live terminal output from the command above. Token values are never printed; the rows below are from the live `/models` response through the patched `fetchCopilotModelCatalog` path.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"proof\": \"patched github-copilot fetchCopilotModelCatalog live /models\",\n  \"baseUrl\": \"https://api.enterprise.githubcopilot.com\",\n  \"modelCount\": 36,\n  \"selected\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"claude-opus-4.7-1m-internal\",\n      \"name\": \"Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context)(Internal only)\",\n      \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n      \"reasoning\": true,\n      \"contextWindow\": 1000000,\n      \"maxTokens\": 64000,\n      \"input\": [\"text\", \"image\"],\n      \"compat\": {\n        \"supportedReasoningEfforts\": [\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"xhigh\", \"max\"]\n      },\n      \"thinkingLevelMap\": { \"xhigh\": \"xhigh\" }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt-5.3-codex\",\n      \"name\": \"GPT-5.3-Codex\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-responses\",\n      \"reasoning\": true,\n      \"contextWindow\": 400000,\n      \"maxTokens\": 128000,\n      \"input\": [\"text\", \"image\"],\n      \"compat\": {\n        \"supportedReasoningEfforts\": [\"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"xhigh\"]\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt-5.4\",\n      \"name\": \"GPT-5.4\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-responses\",\n      \"reasoning\": true,\n      \"contextWindow\": 1050000,\n      \"maxTokens\": 128000,\n      \"input\": [\"text\", \"image\"],\n      \"compat\": {\n        \"supportedReasoningEfforts\": [\"none\", \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"xhigh\"]\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"gpt-5.5\",\n      \"name\": \"GPT-5.5\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-responses\",\n      \"reasoning\": true,\n      \"contextWindow\": 1050000,\n      \"maxTokens\": 128000,\n      \"input\": [\"text\", \"image\"],\n      \"compat\": {\n        \"supportedReasoningEfforts\": [\"none\", \"low\", \"medium\", \"high\", \"xhigh\"]\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"firstFiveIds\": [\n    \"claude-opus-4.6-1m\",\n    \"claude-opus-4.6\",\n    \"claude-opus-4.7-1m-internal\",\n    \"claude-opus-4.7-high\",\n    \"claude-opus-4.7-xhigh\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n- **Observed result after fix:** The patched live catalog path returned 36 Copilot models from the real `/models` endpoint. GPT-5.5 is present with live metadata (`contextWindow: 1050000`, `maxTokens: 128000`, reasoning enabled), and Claude Opus 4.7 1M is present with live Anthropic transport, 1M context, xhigh/max compat, and the xhigh thinking map. Unit coverage now confirms the provider catalog appends fallback rows after live rows and dedupes duplicate ids so live metadata wins.\n- **What was not tested:** Full built `node openclaw.mjs models list --provider github-copilot` from this source checkout was not completed because earlier `pnpm build` hung in `tsdown` at 0% CPU in this local checkout. The patched Copilot token/catalog modules were exercised directly against the live Copilot service instead.\n\nMaintainer compatibility note: if Copilot live discovery is disabled, unauthenticated, or unavailable, this PR now keeps the bounded static fallback catalog visible. When live discovery succeeds, live rows are listed first and fallback rows are appended only for ids absent from the live response.\n",
